    <who name="Dani Megert">daniel_megert</who>
    <bug_when>2013-03-12 11:33:04 -0400</bug_when>
    <thetext>The problem is that after fixing bug 400060 IJavaElement.getAttachedJavadoc(IProgressMonitor) throws a FileNotFoundException for two different cases:

a) the base URL (location of attached Javadoc) is not valid/accessible
b) the base URL is good but there is no Javadoc at that location for the given
   element

For M6 we should just revert (ignore) the FileNotFoundException part. For M7, we need to investigate the cost of checking the base URL and throw the exception there.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
